// safeT PTT iOS — per-machine configuration template.
//
// Copy this file to `Local.xcconfig` (which is gitignored) and replace the
// placeholder URL with your Railway deployment:
//
//     cp Local.example.xcconfig Local.xcconfig
//
// Then re-run `xcodegen generate` (or `./setup.sh`) and rebuild in Xcode.
//
// Auth is now per-user: sign in with your username + password on the login
// screen and the server's JWT is used for every request. The legacy
// `RADIO_API_KEY` is not used by the iOS client anymore.
//
// NOTE: xcconfig treats `//` as a start-of-line-comment, so URL values must
// split the protocol's `//` with `$()` — an empty variable expansion that
// defeats the comment parser. Keep that pattern when editing.

SAFET_API_BASE_URL = https:$()//your-service-name.up.railway.app
